However, there are some questions about his sources and the reliability of his work, as he relied on oral tradition and other sources that may not have been as reliable as we would like today.

Some historians have questioned whether he was more interested in presenting a favorable or unfavorable view of each emperor, depending on his own personal biases and beliefs. This has led to some debates about the accuracy of Suetonius' portrayals, particularly when it comes to controversial figures like Nero or Caligula.

Another criticism of The Twelve Caesars is that it can be repetitive and lacks depth in some areas. Suetonius' biographies were meant to be read as part of a larger work, but many modern readers find them lacking in detail and analysis.

Overall, The Twelve Caesars is still an important work of ancient history that provides valuable insights into the lives and reigns of some of Rome's most important leaders. However, it should be read with a critical eye and taken with a grain of salt, as its accuracy and reliability are not always certain.

I de tidlige år var hip hop knyttet til en ungdomskultur, der fokuserede på at komme forbi et samfund, der forsøgte at afvise dem. Denne kultur blev repræsenteret i sangene, der blev sunget og hjemmestuderet af de unge. De første sange blev sunget i nogle af de største megatræk i New York, inklusive South Bronx og Harlem. 

Hip hop kommer fra afroamerikanske rytmer og melodier og benytter sig af et stort antal instrumenter, inklusive trommer, guitarer, basuner og fløjter. Sangen var oprindeligt sunget af et enkelt sanger og gjort ved hjælp af en enkelt turntable (en slags cd-afspiller). Senere blev der indført andre instrumenter til musikken, hvilket gav den en mere kompleks lyd. 

Den første hip hop sang var "Rapper's Delight", som blev skrevet og sunget af Sugar Hill Gang i 1979. Det er den sang, der gjorde hip hop til en underculture. Denne sang blev også det første rap hit nummer et i USA.

Hip hop er nu et globalt fenomen, der spredte sig til Europa og verden over i løbet af 1980'erne og 1990'erne. I dag er hip hop en kultur, der fortsat udvikles og inspirerer generations over alt rundt om i verden. Hip hop har også blitt brugt som udtryksmåde for social kommentar, politisk aktivisme og udtryk for selvopfattelse for mange kunstnere og grupper.
source: "Hvenær var hip hop fundið upp?"

Fermat's little theorem states that for any integer n, a^p = a (mod n) if p is prime and p > 1. This means that the result of raising a number to the pth power will always be the same modulo n. This can be used to check if an integer is prime by trying to factor it into primes. For example, if we want to check if 23 is prime, we can try raising 2 to the power of each prime less than or equal to 23 and see if the result is 2. If it is, then 23 is not prime, since it cannot be factored into primes. If it isn't, then 23 must be prime since it has only one factor: itself.

This method can be generalized to any base b > 1. For example, for b = 10 and n = 10001, we can try raising 10^i (i = 1,2,...,9999) and see if the result is 10001. If it isn't, then 10001 must be composite since it has more than one factor. If it is, then 10001 must be prime since it has only one factor: itself.

This will create a JSON file called "icelandic_wordlist.json" in the same directory as the Python script, containing a list of Icelandic words and their synsets. The script uses the NLTK library to remove stop words and convert each word to its synset (a dictionary of all its senses).

Here are the steps you need to take to get started with repurposing old clothing and upcycling:

1. Identify the items you want to repurpose or upcycle: Look through your wardrobe and choose items that you no longer wear or that are in good condition but have seen better days.

2. Assess the items: Take a closer look at each item and determine what repurposing or upcycling options are available. For example, a t-shirt may be suitable for sewing into a new garment, while a pair of jeans could be cut into shorts or turned into a rug.

3. Collect the necessary materials: Depending on the project, you may need fabric, buttons, thread, needle and thread, scissors, and other materials. You can find these materials at craft stores or online retailers.

4. Plan the project: Before you begin, plan out your project by sketching out your design and deciding on the details such as fabric selection, pattern creation, and stitching techniques. This will help you stay organized and ensure that your project turns out as you envisioned it.

5. Execute the project: Follow your plan and work carefully to complete your project. Keep in mind that upcycling projects can take more time than simply buying new materials and starting from scratch - but they're worth it in the end!

6. Share your creation: Once you've completed your project, share it with friends and family or on social media to show off your creativity and inspire others to repurpose old clothing too!
